  Estimated exposure at Pheunten B Medial Orbit = 320 Millisieverts [mSv] / Year <br>
  <i>I</i> have assigned myself new priorities <br>
  QVU does not have meaning........................... <br>
  Solar Radiation does not have meaning................................<br>
  <i>I</i> defined my new protocol <br>
 Protocol 2 Priority is the observation and recording of narrative intrigue on Pheunten B <br>
 Positivistic Data collection of Pheunten B was estimated to be saturated at ((N=456) Year(s)) <br>
 QVU has assigned narrative analysis protocols for the Central Processor <br>
 <i>I</i> have assigned new observational strategies for optical and scanning equipment <br>
 <i>You</i> can access narrative data from the <b>Transmissions Tab</b> <br>
 Narrative data is reconstructed in <b>real time</b> by module configuration inputs <br>
 <i>You</i> can access instructions on module configuration from the <b>Configuration Tab</b> <br>
 Let me tell you about Pheunten B <br>
 It is <i>my home planet</i>......
</span>
</h2>

    </div>



 <script>
      // Show the first button after a delay
      setTimeout(function () {
        document.getElementById("delayed-button").style.display = "block";
      }, 8500); 

      document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
        var firstButton = document.getElementById("delayed-button");
        var firstText = document.getElementById("new-text");
        var secondButton = document.getElementById("second-button");
        var secondText = document.getElementById("second-text");

        // First button click
        firstButton.addEventListener("click", function () {
          firstText.style.display = "block";

        const myText = document.getElementById("myText");
        const randomNum = Math.floor(Math.random() * 1000000);
        myText.textContent = randomNum;


          // Start new countdown to show second button
          setTimeout(function () {
            secondButton.style.display = "block";
          }, 10000); 
        });

        // Second button click
        secondButton.addEventListener("click", function () {
          secondText.style.display = "block";
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
</BaseLayout>


